41
00:02:39,708 --> 00:02:44,908
Lupin walked through a field to take a shortcut to the nearest train station.

42
00:02:45,408 --> 00:02:49,908
There, he met someone traveling in the opposite direction.

43
00:02:50,308 --> 00:02:53,408
It was a man about fifty years of age.

44
00:02:53,908 --> 00:02:59,168
He was tall, looked like a foreigner, and carried a walking stick.

45
00:03:00,021 --> 00:03:02,321
The man spoke to Lupin.

46
00:03:03,141 --> 00:03:07,121
Excuse me, sir. Is this the way to the castle?

47
00:03:07,741 --> 00:03:11,321
Yes, it is. They are waiting for you.

48
00:03:11,661 --> 00:03:12,661
Oh?

49
00:03:13,161 --> 00:03:16,961
My friend, Devon, told us last night that you were coming.

50
00:03:17,421 --> 00:03:22,921
I am very happy to be the first person to welcome you, Sherlock Holmes.

51
00:03:26,001 --> 00:03:29,421
There is no one who admires you more than me.

52
00:03:29,923 --> 00:03:33,183
ルポンは彼の言葉の選択をすぐに悔しめました

53
00:03:33,183 --> 00:03:36,703
ホームズは彼をとても近くに見つけました

54
00:03:36,703 --> 00:03:40,323
ルポンは

55
00:03:40,323 --> 00:03:44,183
彼は私を見せる必要があり、私はルポンだと知っていました

56
00:03:44,183 --> 00:03:48,643
